//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_trigger_build}

NOTE: This operation dispatches a container build via the vessel's
{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
using the committed
{rbtgr_build_json}
in its
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}.
All substitution values are baked at inscribe time — zero custom overrides at dispatch.

NOTE: This operation supports concurrent execution per the Concurrent Session Safety invariant.
Each invocation dispatches an independent trigger execution with a unique `BUILD_ID`.
Concurrent builds of the same vessel produce independent images with different
{rbtga_hallmark}
timestamps.

The
{rbtr_director}
dispatches a trigger-based remote container build:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»` is an existing directory
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»/rbrv.env`
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` exists
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel configuration not found"

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source `«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` into current environment
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_sigil} defined and non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. Validate vessel directory name matches `«VESSEL_SIGIL»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if mismatch: "Vessel sigil does not match directory name"

//axhos_step
. *Validate Conjuring Configuration*:
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} defined
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext} defined
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel not configured for conjuring"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Trigger Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TRIGGER_NAME»` from `RBGC_RUBRIC_TRIGGER_PREFIX` + `«VESSEL_SIGIL»`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/list[cloudbuild.triggers.list] with:
... project:
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... filter matching `«TRIGGER_NAME»`
.. {rbbc_require}
exactly one trigger matches
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TRIGGER_ID»` from matching trigger resource
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not found: "Vessel trigger not found"

//axhos_step
. *Dispatch Build via Trigger*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RUBRIC_COMMIT»` as HEAD of the build definition repository
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/run[cloudbuild.triggers.run] with:
... project:
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... triggerId: `«TRIGGER_ID»`
... source.repoSource.commitSha: `«RUBRIC_COMMIT»`
.. Zero custom substitution overrides — all `_RBGY_*` values baked in
{rbtgr_build_json}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_ID»` from response `.metadata.build.id`
.. {rbbc_show}
build dispatched with `«BUILD_ID»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Cloud Console URL for build monitoring

//axhos_step
. *Cloud Build Execution*:
.. NOTE: Build executes via OCI Layout Bridge pattern to solve BuildKit credential isolation. See Trade Study RBSOB for design rationale.
.. {gcb_service}
executes the following phases within the
{rbtgi_depot_project}:
... *Build Phase*: Multi-platform container compilation produces OCI Image Layout artifact in shared workspace. No registry credentials required.
... *Push Phase*: OCI artifact copied to
{rbtgi_repository}
using
{oauth_token}
obtained from
{gcb_service}
metadata server.
... *Platform Split Phase*: Multi-platform OCI layout split to single-platform (linux/amd64) via skopeo (per-platform tag isolation).
... *Manifest Assembly Phase*: Consumer-facing multi-platform manifest list assembled from per-platform tags.
.. All phases execute as
{rbtr_mason}
within the depot infrastructure.

//axhos_step
. *Wait for Build Completion*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/get[cloudbuild.builds.get] with:
... project:
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... buildId: `«BUILD_ID»`
.. Poll every 5 seconds for up to 20 minutes (240 attempts)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_STATUS»` from response `.status`
.. Continue polling while `«BUILD_STATUS»` in [`PENDING`, `QUEUED`, `WORKING`]
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "Build timeout after 20 minutes"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if final status is not `SUCCESS`: "Build failed with status: «BUILD_STATUS»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
build completed successfully
.. {rbbc_show}
{rbtga_hallmark}
tag (dual-timestamp: inscribe + realized)
.. {rbbc_show}
image available in
{rbtgi_repository}

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution builds the container image and stores it in the repository.
{rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed SLSA v1.0 attestation on the built image.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_ark_about}
to assemble metadata, then
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
to verify provenance.

==== Substitution Variable Inventory

All `_RBGY_*` substitution variables are baked into
{rbtgr_build_json}
at inscribe time.
Cloud Build resolves these from the committed JSON — no values are overridden at dispatch.

*Vessel identity*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_MONIKER` | Vessel sigil. Source: {rbrv_sigil}.
| `_RBGY_DOCKERFILE` | Dockerfile path relative to build context. Source: {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}.
| `_RBGY_PLATFORMS` | Target platforms. Source: {rbrv_conjure_platforms}.
|===

*Registry coordinates*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GAR_LOCATION` | Artifact Registry region. Source: {rbrr_gcp_region}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_PROJECT` | Depot project ID. Source: derived `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID` from `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER`.
| `_RBGY_GAR_REPOSITORY` | GAR repository name. Source: derived `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY` from `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER`.
| `_RBGY_GAR_HOST_SUFFIX` | GAR Docker host suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_ARK_BASENAME_IMAGE` | Image artifact basename under the hallmark subtree. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_CRANE_TAR_GZ` | Crane release tarball URL. Source: RBGC constant.
|===

*Provenance*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GIT_COMMIT` | Main repo HEAD SHA. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_GIT_BRANCH` | Main repo branch at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_GIT_REPO` | Main repo identifier (owner/repo).
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_REPO` | Build definition repository URL. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_COMMIT` | Build definition repository HEAD SHA after push. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP` | Inscribe timestamp (`YYMMDDHHMMSS`). Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time. Used by rbgjb01 to construct {rbtga_hallmark}.
|===

Builder image references (step `name:` fields) are resolved to digest-pinned URIs from regime pins at inscribe time.
These are inlined directly into JSON — not expressed as substitution variables.

==== Script Inlining

Step scripts (`rbgjb/*.sh`) are the source of truth for build logic.
At stitch time, each script is read and inlined into the corresponding JSON `args` array of
{rbtgr_build_json}.

Developers edit `rbgjb/*.sh` in the main repo, then run the stitch function to regenerate
{rbtgr_build_json}
with the updated content.

==== Tag Construction

Each build produces a
{rbtga_hallmark}
with dual timestamps:

`c«YYMMDDHHMMSS»-r«YYMMDDHHMMSS»`

* `c«YYMMDDHHMMSS»` — conjure mode prefix + inscribe timestamp, baked as `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP`
* `r«YYMMDDHHMMSS»` — realized timestamp, derived at build time by `rbgjb01-derive-tag-base.sh`

Example: `c260224153022-r260224160530`

Step `rbgjb01` constructs: `HALLMARK="c${_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP}-r$(date -u +%y%m%d%H%M%S)"`

Complete artifact references compose the hallmarks root, the hallmark identifier, and the ark basename with {rbtga_hallmark} as tag:

* {rbtga_ark_image}: `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/«ARK_BASENAME_IMAGE»:«HALLMARK»`

About and vouch artifacts are created by subsequent pipeline stages ({rbtgo_ark_about}, {rbtgo_ark_vouch}).

Multiple builds of the same inscribed JSON sort together by inscribe prefix,
each distinguished by its realized timestamp.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}

NOTE: This operation conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
in
{rbtgi_repository}
by building a container image from a vessel specification. The
{rbtr_director}
performs the build via
{gcb_service}
using direct `builds.create` API submission.

NOTE: Conjure produces both the image and about artifacts in a single Cloud Build job submitted via `builds.create`.
The about steps (`rbgja01`-`rbgja04`) are embedded via stitch alongside the build steps.
The vouch artifact is created by the subsequent {rbtgo_ark_vouch} pipeline stage (always a separate Cloud Build job).

NOTE: The
{rbtga_hallmark}
is minted locally by the
{rbtr_director}
before submission.
The Director knows the complete artifact tag set before the build begins -- naming authority and verification authority are the same entity.

NOTE: The conjure build job runs on the worker pool selected by the vessel's `RBRV_EGRESS_MODE`: tether pool for vessels needing public internet (e.g., `apt-get` in Dockerfile), airgap pool for vessels with all dependencies enshrined in GAR.
The subsequent {rbtgo_ark_vouch} always runs on the airgap pool regardless of vessel egress mode.

NOTE: *Universal reliquary precondition*. Every ordain-path vessel — conjure, bind, and graft — must have `RBRV_RELIQUARY` non-empty before this operation runs. The about/vouch pipeline (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft) consumes reliquary tool images uniformly across all modes; the registry preflight below enforces this.

NOTE: The conjure Cloud Build job carries the {rbsk_in_pool_preflight} as its step 0, ahead of the extract-context step. Conjure populates `_RBGR_ENSHRINE_LOCATOR_n` substitutions from `RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR` slots, so the preflight HEAD-checks each anchored base in addition to the reliquary tools.

The conjure operation:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel contains conjuring configuration (RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE, RBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT)

//axhos_step
. *Registry Preflight*:
.. *Reliquary check*: HEAD request to `«RELIQUARY»/docker:latest` manifest in
{gar_service}.
{rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — on 404, fail with directive to run inscribe first.
The reliquary is a co-versioned set of builder tool images inscribed from upstream into private GAR. Each vessel declares its reliquary; multiple datestamped reliquaries can coexist.
.. *Enshrine check*: For each indexed slot (n = 1, 2, 3) where both
{rbrv_image_origin}
and
{rbrv_image_anchor}
are set:
... Parse
{rbrv_image_anchor}
as a
{rbst_locator}
into package-path and tag
... HEAD request to `«LOCATOR-PATH»:«LOCATOR-TAG»` manifest in
{gar_service}
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — on 404, fail with directive to run {rbtgo_ark_enshrine} first.
Multiple vessels sharing the same anchor need only one enshrine.
.. Preflight prevents wasted
{gcb_service}
submission time on missing images, with copy-paste remediation commands

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Base Images*:
.. For each indexed slot (n = 1, 2, 3) where
{rbrv_image_origin}
is set:
... If
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is present: parse the
{rbst_locator}
and resolve to full GAR image reference (`«GAR-REPO-BASE»/«LOCATOR-PATH»:«LOCATOR-TAG»`)
... If
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is absent: pass
{rbrv_image_origin}
through as the upstream tag (development path)
.. Resolved references become `RBF_IMAGE_n` build-args for the Dockerfile `ARG`/`FROM` pattern

//axhos_step
. *Assign Hallmark*:
.. Mint
{rbtga_hallmark}
locally on the Director's workstation
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK»` -- complete artifact tag set is now known before build submission

//axhos_step
. *Push Pouch*:
.. Package build context (Dockerfile and context files) as a FROM SCRATCH OCI image
.. Push to GAR tagged `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/pouch:«HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_require}
push succeeds -- the pouch delivers build context to
{gcb_service}

//axhos_step
. *Execute Build*:
.. Stitch
{rbtgr_build_json}
with all step image references and substitution variables
.. {rbbc_submit}
`POST «GCB_PROJECT_BUILDS_URL»` with Build resource JSON via `builds.create`
.. All build parameters in stitched
{rbtgr_build_json}
-- zero custom substitution overrides
.. Waits for build completion
.. On success, the
{rbtga_ark_image}
artifact is created with the
{rbtga_hallmark}
.. {rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed attestation on the built image

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_image}

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_hallmark}
The full
{rbtga_hallmark}
string.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_build_id}
The
{gcb_build}
job ID from the `builds.create` submission.
Used by
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
for
{rbtgr_provenance}
verification.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_gar_root}
{gar_service}
registry prefix.
Composable with
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_stem}
Hallmark subtree prefix joining
{gar_service}
root with the hallmark path segment as `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»`.
Composable with basename and `:«HALLMARK»` tag for full artifact references.

//axhoot_typed_output axd_fact
{rbf_fact_ark_yield}
Per-platform
{rbtga_ark_image}
reference.
One fact file per platform discovered during the build.

. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
vessel image built with hallmark tag

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates the
{rbtga_ark_image}
in
{rbtgi_repository}.
The {rbtr_director} retains `«BUILD_ID»` and `«HALLMARK»` from the conjure round-trip.
The `builds.create` job produces both the image and about artifacts under the hallmark subtree (about steps embedded via stitch).
{rbtgo_ark_ordain} chains only {rbtgo_ark_vouch} after the combined job completes, passing `«BUILD_ID»` for DSSE provenance verification.

